                            <comment id="13483095" author="raintung.li" created="Wed, 24 Oct 2012 09:07:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix the bug patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13483290" author="erickerickson" created="Wed, 24 Oct 2012 14:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Raintung is correct. In fact, deleteInstanceDir seems to be completely broken unless you specify an absolute dir.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a reworked patch because it seems like the trap here (CoreContainer.getInstanceDir()) is just laying in wait for the unwary. I&apos;ve added a new method getRawInstanceDir and refactored the uses of getInstanceDir to use the right one. I wouldn&apos;t dare return the new getInstanceDir to, say, the snapshooter code, and the code that writes solr.xml back out would also be broken if it used the (new) getInstanceDir().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are no objections, I&apos;ll commit this tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks  Raintung! Your patch provided me a &lt;em&gt;much&lt;/em&gt; easier time tackling this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
